description: As the various factions swirling around Jim continue to come into focus, Malebolgia makes his move. He confronts Clown about the missing piece of his power and sets up a showdown that will test Jim's true power.
name: The Gathering Storm, Part 5 (of 6)

description: Reprinted The Iron Legion story from Doctor Who Weekly #1-8, plus K-9's Finest Hour from Doctor Who Weekly #12. Also included pin-ups of the first four Doctors (which was all the Doctors, at the time of publication) and features on the Cybermen and Daleks.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description:
As well as several features, reprinted from various issues of Doctor Who Weekly and Doctor Who Monthly, the Summer Special also includes two reprinted comic strips:

Timeslip, from Doctor Who Weekly #17-18

Business as Usual, a back-up strip starring the Autons, from Doctor Who Weekly #40-43.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description:
The first Doctor Who Special to include new comic strips, rather than reprints, alongside the usual features about the TV show Doctor Who. The strips, neither of which featured the Doctor himself, except as a narrator, were:

Tales of the Time Lords: Minatorius - which followed the story of a novice Time Lord, Cargan, on a visit to the city Minatorius. The writing is attributed to Maxwell Stockbridge, an alias used by various Marvel UK writers.

Skywatch-7 (part two) - concluding a tale about an isolated Arctic UNIT base menaced by a Zygon. Part One was a back-up in Doctor Who Monthly #58, with part two published here due to the creative team missing their deadline for the regular magazine. Like the other comic strip, writing is attributed to Maxwell Storckbridge.
name: Doctor Who Winter Special

description:
Includes two new comic strips alongside the usual features and articles about the Doctor Who TV show. Neither strip involves the Doctor; instead both are new adventures of characters the Doctor met in the Doctor Who Monthly #57-58 story "The Freefall Warriors."

The Fabulous Idiot follows alien science fiction novelist Ivan Asimoff as he tried to finish his latest book.

A Ship Called Sudden Death saw alien stunt pilot Big Cat, one of the Freefall Warriors, take on an old adversary, Shaman Kahn.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: What will Detective Walt Booker sacrifice, to what gods? And is he looking for redemption or revenge? In part three of BRUBAKER and PHILLIPS' new horror/noir masterpiece, the threads of the first arc twist together... into a noose around the neck of a corrupt cop in late '50s San Francisco.

As well as the usual features and articles based on the TV series Doctor Who, the special included a humorous strip by Tim Quinn and Dicky Howett:

"So you think you would make a good companion for Dr. Who!"
name: Doctor Who Winter Special

description:
Unlike previous specials, this publication had no articles or features, but instead reprinted past stories from Doctor Who Weekly and Doctor Who Monthly with a new illustrated text story providing a linking narrative.

Catalogue of Events sees the Doctor discover a Time Lord facility, the Events Library, where events (actual pieces of reality), rather than stories, are stored, and he is shown one of his own past adventures, Junkyard Demon (from Doctor Who Monthly #58-59), and the tale of Abslom Daak, Dalek Killer (from Doctor Who Weekly #17-22).
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description:
Mainly filled with interviews of past cast and crew of the Doctor Who TV show, this special also included a humorous strip by Tim Quinn and Dicky Howett:

"Doctor Who: An Unearthly Child (The Unscreened Edition)"
name: Doctor Who Winter Special 1983/1984

description: With a squarebound spine rathern than staples, and reprinting early Doctor Who Weekly strips in full colour (using, presumably, the colorised reprints done for Marvel Premiere, whose first two Doctor Who covers were also reprinted), this Special was closer in style to a graphic novel. It reprinted The Iron Legion from Doctor Who Weekly #1-8 and K-9's Finest Hour from Doctor Who Weekly #12.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description:
Metropolis has been captured! To save it, Superman must push the limits of his nascent powers as never before! Aboard the ship that has the city captive, The Man of Steel finds an important tool that may help him defeat Metal-zero and his boss!

And as Superman fights foes in the sky, Steel must do what he can to protect those still in danger on the ground in a backup story by Sholly Fisch and Brad Walker!
name: Superman's Doomsday Decision; Meanwhile...

description:
Celebrated Doctor Who's 25th Anniversary with articles and interviews, plus the illustrated prose story Scream of the Silent, and a humourous strip by Tim Quinn and Dicky Howett:

Ever wondered what happened at the Auditions for the Seven Doctors?
name: Doctor Who 25th Anniversary Special

description: As well as articles and an interview with Sophie Aldred, the actress who played Ace on Doctor Who, this special included two comic strips, the humourous Comic Assassins: The Five Doctors and Paul Cornell's Seaside Rendezvous. Despite Lee Sullivan's cover illustration, K-9, Sea Devils, Daleks, Haemovores and the Skarasen do not appear in the strip.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: They've come to steal Earth's gravity! When a scientific experiment tears a hole in the barrier between dimensions, gravity miners from a forbidden universe invade our world! Can Stormwatch – with their ranks depleted after the cataclysmic events of last issue – find a way to repel alien excavators that shred our reality with every touch?
name: Supercritical, Part One

description: Most of this Special's articles are presented as being from within the Doctor Who universe and taken from The Metropolitan newspaper, exposing facts about the top-secret organisation UNIT. The issue also includes two prose shorts, Dan Abnett's Listening Watch and A Wee Deoch an...?, written by Colin Baker, the actor who played the sixth Doctor on television. Dan Abnett also wrote the issue's comic strip, The Man in the Ion Mask, detailing the third Doctor preventing the Master escaping from UNIT custody following his capture at the end of the TV story The Daemons.
name: Doctor Who Winter Special: UNIT Exposed

description: A special based around popular Doctor Who companion Sarah Jane Smith, with some articles written as if coming from within the Doctor Who universe, such as an unofficial biography of Sarah Jane. Also includes three short prose stories, Girls' Night In, Playtime and Fond Memories, the last of which was written by Nicholas Courtney, who played the Brigadier alongside Lis Sladen's Sarah Jane, plus a comic strip, City of Devils, starring Sarah and K-9.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: Themed around the Doctor's people, the Time Lords. Though depicted on the cover, neither the Master nor the Rani appear in the comic strip Flashback. The strip's antagonist, the Time Lord Magnus, sometimes mistaken by readers for an early incarnation of the Master, was confirmed in Doctor Who tie-in novels to be the War Chief, who appeared in the TV story The War Games.
name: Doctor Who Winter Special

description: A special themed around the Doctor's greatest foes, the Daleks. Though included on Steve Whitaker's cover, Davros does not appear in the issue's comic strip, Bringer of Darkness.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: One's past can be a powerful motivator, or a crippling adversary. Memories linger, and the scars of youth can last forever. As Greg awakens from surgery, things begin to come unhinged as complications arise with his new adrenaline implant.

With Doctor Who having, at the time of publication, been off the air for just under five years, this special was themed around the beginning and end of the series, with articles on the show's first and last stories, and a flip cover showing both the first Doctor and the seventh (last at that time) in the first and last TV stories. The issue included two comic strips, Are You Listening?, which starred the first Doctor, and Younger and Wiser, which starred the seventh and was a sequel to Are You Listening?
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: Having lost all control when his new implant was fully activated, and nearly killing Matt, Greg has fled the base and made his way into the DC metro area. It's up to Matt to track down his brother-in-arms and bring him back before he causes any harm to himself, the city, or its civilians. But what is it about the 'upgrade' that triggered Greg's mental break? Could there be a sinister secret hiding within the Project Red Spike files?

Themed around the stories of Robert Holmes, one of Doctor Who's longest serving and most respected script writers. Though on the cover, the Sontarans do not appear in the comic strip, Plastic Millenium (sic).
name: Doctor Who Winter Special

description: Where does one draw the line in the sand? How do we define the moment when once unwavering trust is called into question? As Matt and Greg battle it out on the Lincoln Memorial, harsh truths are revealed on the Project Red Spike base.

MINISERIES CONCLUSION

After the casualties mount up Coughlin vies for control of Red Spike. If he does, Moyer will be court-martialed. Matt Cutler is the golden ticket each side needs to win. Power breeds arrogance and often times, relinquishing that power is the most difficult part of having had it in the first place. Will Moyer's stand be enough to protect his program? Will Matt stand with his Mentor? Or is Red Spike destined to be torn down by its own favored son? Find out in this thrilling climax of RED SPIKE's first mission.

Themed around Doctor Who's sixteenth series, which was the first series to have a story arc running through all the episodes, the Doctor's search for the six segments of the reality-controlling Key to Time. Included a comic strip, The Seventh Segment.
name: Doctor Who Summer Special

description: The penultimate Doctor Who Seasonal Special, themed around the 1960s Doctor Who movies by Amicus, Dr. Who and the Daleks and Daleks: Invasion Earth 2150 AD. Articles covered the two movies, while the comic strip featured Doctor Who, the human version of the Doctor from the films, rather than the Time Lord seen in the TV show, and his companions, his niece Louise, and granddaughter Susan Who (not Susan Foreman, as in the TV series), in a sequel to the movies, Daleks Versus The Martians.
name: Doctor Who Spring Special

description: With the Signal Men defeated and Earth saved from certain annihilation, the members of Justice League International expected to bask in glory and appreciation. Such is not the case as a new threat, one far more dangerous than anyone dared suspect, emerges and attacks with dire results, forever altering the team and sending it in a bold, new and unexpected direction.
name: Breakdown

description: Static seeks information at S.T.A.R. Labs in regard to his sisters, only to discover that they've walked in on a heist. Introducing the intangible Phayze, who's out to steal tech that could change the world. How can Static defeat a villain he can't touch, protect his sisters from rampaging drones, and keep his alias a secret? It's just another spark of excitement for this electromagnetic teenager! Featuring the debut of new series new writer Marc Bernardin (THE AUTHORITY, THE HIGHWAYMEN, TV's Alphas) as we begin an exciting new chapter in a young hero's story.
name: Out of Phayze

description: Warren Ellis introduces you to the sultry Anna Mercury in this collection of first action-packed series! Dancing amid the spires of a city called New Ataraxia, there is a woman who can cloud men's minds, leap across buildings as if weightless, unerringly fire twin automatic pistols in the most insane conditions, and disappear in a crowded room. She fights against the political repression of an insane technocratic society, and she comes from a place that no-one in New Ataraxia has ever heard of. And she's got one hour to save the city from itself. A high-octane blend of The Shadow, Tomb Raider, retro-punk science fiction and 21st-century Weird Pulp action, Anna Mercury is a headlong adventure serial about a beautiful and mysterious spy-adventurer who is not what she seems! Anna Mercury Volume 1 features all five of the original issues with art by all-new talent Facundo Percio as well as a special super-sized cover gallery!
name: The Cutter

description: Collects : Generation Hope (2011) #03,04 - New Mutants (2009) #20 - Uncanny X-Force (2010) #05.1 -X-23 (2010) #04 - X-Factor (2006) #212
Collects : Generation Hope (2011) #05 - New Mutants (2009) #21 - Uncanny X-Force (2010) #05 -X-23 (2010) #05,06 - X-Factor (2006) #213

Introducing the Extreme Universe's government superteam against the supernatural... the WAR DOGS. After the murder of the Torment Killer, Ned Crowley, the New Church of the People becomes a media frenzy. With Priest on the run, it's up to Avengelyne to get to him before the War Dogs execute their orders to kill on sight. Plus, an "Extreme Origins" back-up written by MARK POULTON with art by a guest artist!
name: The Hunt, Part 1

description: Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, The Far Side, Outland, Doonesbury, and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)

volume.name: Arf! The Life and Times of Little Orphan Annie

description:
Kir Kanos, the last surviving member of the Emperor's Royal Guard, finds himself teamed with his former enemy Mirith Sinn on a mission for the New Republic. But their secret parley with an Imperial representative becomes an ambush from which some will not return!

Meanwhile, the Imperial hardliners reveal their true target!
name: Part Five (of Six)

volume.name: Star Wars: Crimson Empire III - Empire Lost

description:
Spider-Man and the Human Torch are trapped on a space station full of octo-zombies plummeting toward the Earth! This best buds super team-up is running out of air and running out of time! The final stage of Doc Ock's master plan begins here!

Complete Plot

The story starts where the last issue left off; Spider-Man, Human Torch, and John Jameson are surrounded by the crew of the Apogee 1 Space Station. The crew are under the control of tiny octobots and are attacking the heroes. Johnny Storm flames on and flies them all to safety. He had to flame off though because he was burning off all the oxygen that the station has left. The trio make their way towards Storm's Pogo Plane but it gets blown up by an angry Doctor Octopus. The team then attempt to make it to the space shuttle but that also gets blown up.

When all hope seems lost, Spider-Man develops a plan to save them all. If they deplete the station of its oxygen supply then the Octobot-controlled crew will be knocked unconscious because they still need air to breathe. Doctor Octopus sees what is happening and who is ultimately responsible for his failed plan (Spider-Man) so he sends the station plummeting to the Earth.

The heroes and the unconscious crew manage to escape the doomed space station by stowing away within the Deep Space Sensory Deprivation Chamber that is a component of the station.

They crash land into the water and the crew is saved by passing boats. In the midst of all the chaos of plummeting to the earth, Johnny Storm manages to direct their crash landing to the waters off the coast of Daytona Beach during spring break.

The final scene cuts to Doctor Octopus and the Sinister Six. Doctor Octopus says that it is time to activate his last master plan.
name: The Galaxy's Greatest Super-Hero. Part Two

description: News of the new Spider-Man has finally spread to some very familiar characters! The Scorpion is in New York and the big apple is feeling the sting! What does uncle Aaron have planned for Miles and his new powers?
name: The Scorpion's Sting

description: Winter Soldier versus Doctor Doom! Nuff Said!
name: The Longest Winter, Part 3

description: The conclusion of Tabula Rasa! Namor does the unthinkable to save the day.
name: Tabula Rasa, Conclusion

description:
Mephisto offers a deal the heroes might not be able to refuse. Before Ghost Rider's decision rips this new team apart, can they work together to stop Blackheart? Cap and The Avengers might have something to say about the fallout.

Complete Plot

SPOILER WARNING: Click here to reveal hidden content.
The issue opens with a showgirl being chased by a pack of goat-like demons, with Flash Thompson narrating the conditions of the Hell that has taken over Las Vegas. After killing one of the demons, Flash attempts to stop the showgirl from running away, but unfortunately she is caught by the demon pack, and subsequently torn apart. While the demons turn to Flash, and he begins to run out of ammunition, he expresses regret for relinquishing his symbiote to Thaddeus Ross a.k.a. Red Hulk.

The scene then shifts to Red Hulk, who is in possession of both the Spirit of Vengeance and the Symbiote, and is fighting Blackheart. The combined possession generates an interesting personality within the one character.

The scene then shifts to X-23 at the Centrifuge, where she is giving direction to a struggling Johnny Blaze. She tells him that he must change direction when she says so that she can blow up the passage way. However, Gari Oyle then arrives, injuring X-23 and then turning her claws to copper dust.

The scene then shifts back to Flash, who is fending off the horde, and expressing regret for what he has said to Betty and his mother. Suddenly, Alejandra arrives in a car, rescuing Thompson. They argue over what is going on, with Alejandra threatening murder in order to have the Spirit of Vengeance returned to her, but Flash forces her to help by putting her at gunpoint.

Back to Hulk, he attempts to use the Penance Stare on Blackheart, but discovers that it merely strengths him, and is then knocked back by the immense power that the demon now possesses.

Back to X-23, Gari Oyle is brutalising her, causing grievous injury. Laura attempts to attach some explosives to the gargoyle's back, but is slapped before she can detonate. Gari Oyle then lifts X-23, and bites deep into her neck, almost decapitating her. However, Flash and Alejandra arrive, with Flash shooting at Gari as Alejandra drives. However, she betrays Flash when he points the gun away from her head, knocking him out of the car and leaving him at the mercy of Oyle. We then see a giant Blackheart catching Hulk, and launching him far away. Gari leaves Flash and X-23 to kill Johnny Blaze, but Flash is able to reach his gun to shoot the C-4 on her back, defeating her.

The scene shifts to Hulk and Blackheart once more, where we see that the latter believes himself triumphant, but Hulk has found H'Elian's Mirror Cauldron, and summons forth Blackheart's Antithesis, which takes the form of a shining, white-blue angelic being. Flash then orders Johnny Blaze to reverse rotation, to suck Hell back down to where it belongs. Blackheart's Antithesis then shines even brighter, engulfing him in a bright light. Las Vegas returns to a somewhat normal state, and we find Hulk in the middle of the street.

Alejandra orders him to return the Spirit of Vengeance, which then leaves Thaddeus to return to her, who then leaves on her motorcycle, the Ghost Rider once more. Hulk then returns the symbiote to Flash, who is Venom once again. However, Captain America, Dr. Strange, Hellstorm, Beast and Giant-Man arrive, to apprehend Venom. However, Hulk defends him, and Beast suggests they come to a compromise where they ensure the symbiote remains dormant. Captain America then says that they can find a way to help him...as long as he returns his bike.

Dr. Strange notices that Hellstorm is surprisingly distant. He has noticed that Flash, Laura and Thaddeus each bear an upside-down pentagram, a symbol of Mephisto. We then shift to Mephisto himself, who is now dominant over Blackheart and Gari Oyle. He offers them a new casino to run, and then transports them to a 'family-friendly' casino, where they are handed mops by their new boss. Mephisto looks on, content with his trick.

End.

"Time For a Change" - When Archie and Mr. Weatherbee volunteer to be guinea pigs in Dilton's I.Q. analyzer for the science fair, something goes horribly wrong! Instead of measuring their brain power, the experiment causes them to switch bodies! Worst of all, Archie has a date planned with Veronica and Mr. Weatherbee will be giving an important speech to the school board before the effect wears off. Will student and principle manage to spend a day in each other's shoes without everything falling to shambles?
name: Time For a Change

description: The big climax that sets the stage big time for what is to come in 2012! - Deaths and departures! The final fate of the Scarlet Witch. A new lineup and a new direction for the Young Avengers.

Logan, Yukio, and Amiko invade the secret cave headquarters of The Hand to save The Silver Samurai -- The big finale of The Hand / Yakuza War! The Puppetmaster is finally revealed. This ending will forever change the landscape for Wolverine in Japan.
name: Back in Japan, Part 3

description: Spinning directly out of Uncanny X-Force... The Amazing X-Men have lost and the evil Weapon X is more powerful than ever. Jean Grey and Sabretooth are at their lowest. Who are the X-Terminated?
name: X

description: Quentin loses control over the construct as Logan's health further deteriorates! To regain command of his psychic videogame, Quentin must enter the construct as a player!
name: Alpha & Omega, Part 3

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

volume.name: Wolverine and the X-Men: Alpha & Omega

description: GUEST-STARRING WITCHBLADE! The hunt for a piece of the One True Cross leads Patience and Kristof to the US, where Patience is reunited with an old friend - Sara Pezzini! Together will the Artifact bearers be able to recover the relic from Patience's newest adversary? RON MARZ (ARTIFACTS, WITCHBLADE), NELSON BLAKE II (PILOT SEASON: MURDERER) and DAVID MARQUEZ (Secret Warriors, Days Missing) continue the fan favorite series!
name: The One, True Cross, Part 3

description: Who is the greatest lost love of Dr. Strange's life? Why does a young-gun Magician have Strange in his sights? What is the Concordance Engine?
name: Misfits 1: Strange/ The French Drop

description: It's cowboys vs. Indians vs. outlaws as the battle for the bounty begins. But whoever wins must drag a vicious zombie across Texas to claim their reward!
Guest-starring the Runaways! Giant-Man, Victor Reptil, and Chase... Lightspeed and Karolina... what are the connections that make these combustible crews collide?
name: War With The Runaways, Pt. 1 of 2: Homecoming

description: The X-Men Fight To Rescue Jubilee From The Hands Of Her Vampire Brethren! The Forgiven Fight To Protect Their Own! Featuring The Deadliest Mercenaries In The Entire Marvel Universe!
name: Open Contract, Part Two

description: Red Hulk versus The Eternals! Guest appearance from Hercules! Has Red Hulk set in motion the end of the World???
name: The Incident

description: The X-Club Fights Nazis! With Science! And The Villain Responsible For Framing The X-Men Is Revealed...
name: We Do Science!, Part Four

description: Valkyrie stands alone against the terrifying power of the D.O.A. while Sin brings her Earth-shattering plans to completion! This deadly plot brings in a host of Marvel's Mightiest Heroes, as a universe fights for survival! Valkyrie faces a shocking fate as the Final Sleeper awakens on the road to the pulse-pounding climax of The Fearless, don't miss it!
name: Awakenings

description: Who will win the clash of the criminal masterminds in this shocking series finale? Featuring cult faves like Tiger Shark, Avalanche, Shocker, and Scourge!
name: No Strings

description: The origin of Roadblock! While Roadblock is in a deadly race against time to rescue a childhood friend from the clutches of the enemy, we learn the secrets that shaped the Joe's heavy ordinance officer. Meanwhile-Snake Eyes is in hot pursuit, and he's not taking any prisoners.
The Unbinding Stone... Unbound! Thor vs. the collapse of space and time! The hidden quest of the Eternals revealed!
name: Part 5 of 5

description: Fright-master Steve Niles continues his all-new 30 DAYS OF NIGHT ongoing series, with regular cover artist Davide Furnó providing interior art! A hero from the past becomes our worst nightmare, as vampires declare war on the world.

Lex Luthor and the remaining super powered heroes on Earth have sprung their trap on Brainiac...and the real war begins! The events in this issue will be talked about for years to come!

General Notes

Cyborg, Hourman, Blue Devil, Bombshell, Zatanna, Green Arrow, Wildcat, Jimmy Olsen, Wonder Girl, and Big Barda appear only on the cover.
name: Battle!

description: Betty in "Shop Till You Drop!" - After Betty does Veronica the favor of picking up a gift for one of her society friends, the good deed turns into a after school job as a personal shopper. But when her latest client wants Betty to buy a present to impress Archie, she'll be forced to decide between doing a good job or losing her eligible bachelor! How will Betty choose?
name: Shop Till You Drop!
